XXVI. Great use is also made of verdigris. There are several ways of making it; it ⁰ is scraped off the stone from which copper is smested, or by (ἱ drilling holes in white copper b and hanging it up in casks over strong vinegar which is stopped with a lid3 the verdigris is of much better quality if the same process is performed with scales of copper. Some people put the actual vessels, made of white copper, into vinegar in earthenware jars, and nine days later serape them.
